data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
1. Wash and finely chop berries, roughly toss with berries and pour into a heated sauce pan on medium heat.
2. Cook for 2 hours, occasionally stirring.
3. Once mixture has thickened, remove from heat and immediently pour on prepped berries.
4. Put two slices of berries together to form sandwich.
5. Enjoy!
